The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
		 Wednesday, June 23, 2004  BRIEFS
				 																																	Calcutta, June 22: Ministries that fell vacant when Buddhadeb Bhattacharjees cabinet was rightsized and as Mohammad Salim became an MP were reallocated today.				 																																	The chief minister retained Salims minority development and welfare and self-employment for urban unemployed portfolios. His other ministry, youth services, was allotted to transport and sports minister Subhas Chakraborty. Technical education, which was also handled by Salim, was allotted to Banshagopal Chowdhury, the cottage and small-scale industries minister.				 																																	Cooperation minister Naren De, will now be the food and supplies minister. Kalimuddin Shams had quit the ministry. Des department will be handled by relief minister Hafiz Alam Sairani. Amal Roys irrigation and waterways was allotted to Ganesh Mondol, who used to be the minister of state for the department.				 																																	Howrah: Manas Saha, 21, who had earlier represented Bengal in the junior national boxing championships, was shot at Kajipara in Shibpur on Tuesday evening. He was admitted to SSKM hospital, where his condition was said to be critical. Police said the resident of Sankrail, about 15 km from Calcutta, was attacked when waiting for a bus after practice at the district boxing association.				 																																	Calcutta: The high court on Wednesday asked the joint secretary of the land and land reforms department to appear after a fortnight. He has to clarify then what law empowered him to form a committee to decide on compensation to those whose land had been acquired by the Haldia Development Authority. 
